	<section class="section-paragraph section-faqs">
		<div class="container">
			<h2 class="section-title">Instagram Ads FAQs</h2>
			<div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/FAQPage" class="row">
				<div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
					<div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
						<div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse1">
							<h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">What are Instagram Ads?</h3>
						</div>
						<div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse1" class="collapse">
							<div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
								<p>If your brand is looking to reach its customers with a greater strike rate, Instagram ads are how you can make it happen. As these highly visual ads look much the same as regular posts, these online advertisements appear in several high-profile positions, including the Feed, Stories, Explore and more. With several different ad formats to choose from, you can closely align your campaign with your business objectives, giving you a great chance of experiencing a top ROI.</p>

								<p>With Instagram featuring well over a billion active monthly users, planning and implementing a detailed campaign can deliver your business a massive amount of leads. As the nature of Instagram ads gives you a fantastic opportunity to showcase your brand’s personality, you can drive more followers to your profile and get them to take action on your posts. Whether you design an entire Instagram ad campaign or promote a recent post from in-app, the rewards can be simply incredible.</p>

							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
					<div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
						<div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse2">
							<h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">How can I get started with Instagram ads?</h3>
						</div>
						<div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse2" class="collapse">
							<div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
								<p>Part of the appeal of an Instagram ad campaign is that it’s remarkably easy for brands operating at every scale to get started. The first thing you need to do is connect your Facebook page to your Instagram account before heading to the Facebook Business Manager dashboard to fine-tune your approach. Alongside a clear understanding of your budget and your campaign goals, set an appropriate objective and enter the details of your ad set.</p>

								<p>Next, you’ll have to think carefully about your targeting. Depending on the demographics of your ideal target market, you can position your campaign to reach users based on their location, interests, behaviours and more. After uploading your optimised creative, you can submit your advertisement for approval. But this isn’t the end of your campaign. You should also install the Facebook pixel on your website, which ensures you can track website traffic and target them with remarketing strategies.</p>

							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
					<div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
						<div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse3">
							<h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">Why are Instagram ads important?</h3>
						</div>
						<div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse3" class="collapse">
							<div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
								<p>Instagram is not only one of the biggest social media platforms in the entire world, it’s also home to a wonderfully engaged user base that spends loads of time on the platform. In fact, Instagram users spend an estimated 30 minutes every day scrolling the feed, while 81% of the people use Instagram to research new products and services. This means your business has the chance to reach new audiences and level the playing field with a comprehensive advertising campaign.
								</p>
								<p>No matter what demographics and audiences you’re trying to convert, Instagram ads can be carefully targeted to a precise customer base that cares about your products and services. With businesses across virtually every industry able to develop content that skyrockets their brand awareness, achieving your marketing goals is made simple with an expert-led Instagram advertising campaign. As the team at First Page can deliver outstanding experimentation and analysis while controlling your budget, outgrowing your rivals is within reach.</p>

							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
					<div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
						<div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse4">
							<h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">How does Instagram ad targeting work?</h3>
						</div>
						<div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse4" class="collapse">
							<div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
								<p>Instagram ads deliver outstanding results for businesses because they can be targeted to a remarkably precise customer base. By developing detailed personas of your ideal audience, you can push the platform’s features to the limit. For example, location-based targeting allows brands to reach consumers based on their country, state, postcode or even a specific address radius. This means businesses can target local consumers who live within touching distance of their brick-and-mortar storefront, driving more customers to visit and make a purchase.</p>
								<p>Brands can also target Instagram ads based on age, gender and language, helping you reach a customer base that fits neatly within your established audience personas. As Instagram keeps track of what kind of content users engage with on the platform, interest-based targeting is great for attracting an audience that has displayed a fascination with like-minded businesses. Finally, behaviour-based targeting ensures you can capitalise on potential customers who have purchased similar products or have certain device usage traits.</p>

							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
					<div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
						<div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse5">
							<h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">What’s the difference between Instagram and Facebook ads?</h3>
						</div>
						<div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse5" class="collapse">
							<div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
								<p>Since Instagram was acquired by Facebook in 2012, many business owners struggle to choose between these social media platforms for their advertising needs. With campaigns for both platforms organised through the Facebook Ads Manager, some similarities ensure reaching your target market across either site is possible. Yet there are even more differences that mean you’ll want to think carefully about which campaign makes sense before you invest your hard-earned cash.</p>

								<p>Instagram is hugely popular amongst young adults and teens compared to Facebook. If you have a product aimed at this target market, Instagram ads might end up being the smarter choice, with custom and lookalike campaigns proven to be highly effective. Meanwhile, Facebook has an even larger reach, so businesses seeking maximum brand awareness may opt for this platform instead. However, Instagram engagement is unmatched for brands with visual products that benefit most from 15-60 second video ads and compelling branded content.</p>

							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
					<div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
						<div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse6">
							<h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">What is a custom audience?
							</h3>
						</div>
						<div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse6" class="collapse">
							<div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
								<p>When you set up an Instagram advertising campaign, the standard approach is to target your audience based on specific demographic or psychographic filters like interests and past behaviour. However, brands can also choose to create their own custom audience from a private source of information. For example, a custom audience on Instagram can be based on website traffic, a certain app activity or previous engagement with your content. As these people have already displayed an interest in your business, reaching them with targeted advertisements can deliver amazing results.</p>

								<p>To get started, you’ll need to prepare your customer database in advance. This is because your custom audience information needs to include so-called “identifiers”, which includes snippets of personal data such as a photo number, email address or home address. After making sure you’ve input this information correctly, you can submit your custom audience through the Facebook Business Manager and wait for confirmation that it’s ready to go.
								</p>

							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
					<div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
						<div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse7">
							<h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">What are the types of Instagram ads?
							</h3>
						</div>
